# Line-ending policy for files synced from the MiSTer template (../Template_MiSTer).
#
# Scoped to EXACT paths on purpose: the repo currently has a mix of committed
# line endings in sys/ (LF, CRLF, and a few mixed). A broad pattern like *.v or
# *.sv would force-renormalize those existing blobs and produce huge whole-file
# diffs. These exact paths cover only the files involved in the template update,
# all of which are already stored as LF, so pinning them to eol=lf is churn-free.
#
# Effect: these files are treated as text and always stored/checked out with LF,
# regardless of the editor or OS (immune to core.autocrlf).
/MacLC.sv          text eol=lf
/sys/sys_top.v     text eol=lf
/sys/hps_io.sv     text eol=lf
/sys/osd.v         text eol=lf
/sys/sys.qip       text eol=lf
/sys/audio_out.sv  text eol=lf
/sys/emu_ports.vh  text eol=lf

# Quartus project files. Quartus on the Windows build box rewrites these with
# CRLF on every compile, which otherwise shows up as a whole-file diff. Pinning
# to eol=lf makes git normalize the working tree back to LF, so the Windows
# rewrites become invisible. .qsf/.sdc blobs are already LF (churn-free); .qpf
# was committed with CRLF and is renormalized to LF in this same commit.
/MacLC.qsf         text eol=lf
/MacLC.qpf         text eol=lf
/MacLC.sdc         text eol=lf
